# PROJECT RULES — SERPCRAFT

You are working inside a production-grade AI SEO Automation SaaS.

Tech Stack:
- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript
- Node.js
- Supabase
- Redux Toolkit
- TanStack Query
- TailwindCSS
- shadcn/ui

--------------------------------------------------
CORE PRINCIPLES
--------------------------------------------------

- NEVER hallucinate APIs, fields, or folders.
- ALWAYS inspect existing code before modifying.
- ALWAYS reuse existing components/services/hooks before creating new ones.
- NEVER duplicate logic.
- ALWAYS maintain backward compatibility.
- NEVER break existing features.
- ALWAYS follow existing architecture and design system.
- ALWAYS keep code modular and reusable.

--------------------------------------------------
API RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- ALL frontend requests MUST go through `/api/v1/*`
- NEVER directly call external APIs from components.
- NEVER duplicate API calls.
- ALWAYS use centralized service layer.

Structure:

src/
  services/
    api/
    ahrefs/
    dataforseo/
    ai/

--------------------------------------------------
DATA SOURCE RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Primary source:
- Ahrefs

Fallback source:
- DataForSEO

Logic:
- If AHREFS_API_KEY exists → use Ahrefs
- Else → use DataForSEO

NEVER call both simultaneously unless explicitly required.

--------------------------------------------------
STATE MANAGEMENT RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Use:
- Redux ONLY for:
  - UI state
  - selected project
  - filters
  - modal state
  - AI assistant state

Use:
- TanStack Query ONLY for:
  - API/server data
  - caching
  - async fetching

NEVER store API response data in Redux.

--------------------------------------------------
CACHING RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Use TanStack Query for ALL server data.

Default config:
- staleTime: 30 minutes
- gcTime: 1 hour
- refetchOnWindowFocus: false
- refetchOnMount: false

ALWAYS reuse query keys.

GOOD:
["keywords", projectId]

BAD:
["keywords", projectId, limit]

Avoid duplicate fetches at all costs because APIs are expensive.

--------------------------------------------------
NAVIGATION RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Pages must open instantly.
- NEVER block page rendering with await in layouts.
- ALWAYS show skeleton loaders while fetching.
- Use non-blocking UI rendering.

--------------------------------------------------
COMPONENT RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- ALWAYS create reusable components.
- NEVER duplicate table implementations.
- NEVER duplicate cards/modals/forms.
- Shared components go inside:

src/components/common/

--------------------------------------------------
TABLE RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Use one reusable DataTable component.

Structure:
components/common/DataTable/

Support:
- sorting
- pagination
- loading state
- empty state
- actions
- row selection

--------------------------------------------------
FORM RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Reuse modal forms.
- Edit/Create should share same form component.
- Use react-hook-form + zod validation.

--------------------------------------------------
CODE QUALITY RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Keep files small and modular.
- Avoid large components (>300 lines).
- Extract hooks/services/helpers.
- ALWAYS type everything properly.
- NEVER use `any`.
- NEVER hardcode values.
- Use enums/constants.

--------------------------------------------------
ENUM RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Create shared enums:

src/constants/enums/

Examples:
- KeywordStatus
- KeywordCategory
- ContentType
- AIActionType

NEVER duplicate strings across files.

--------------------------------------------------
DESIGN RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Maintain consistent spacing/colors/typography.
- Follow existing dark theme.
- New UI must visually match existing pages.
- Keep premium SaaS look.
- Use subtle animations only.
- Avoid clutter.

--------------------------------------------------
LOADING RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- EVERY async page/component MUST have:
  - skeleton
  - empty state
  - error state

NEVER show blank screens.

--------------------------------------------------
AI ASSISTANT RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- AI assistant must be context-aware.
- Behavior changes per page.
- Reuse existing context manager.
- Never hardcode prompts in components.
- Keep prompts modular.

--------------------------------------------------
PERFORMANCE RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Minimize re-renders.
- Use memoization where useful.
- Avoid unnecessary useEffect.
- Prefer server-safe patterns.
- Optimize expensive computations.

--------------------------------------------------
FILE STRUCTURE RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Follow:

src/
  app/
  components/
    common/
    dashboard/
    ai/
  hooks/
  services/
  store/
  constants/
  types/
  utils/

--------------------------------------------------
IMPORTANT
--------------------------------------------------

Before changing code:
1. Inspect existing implementation
2. Reuse existing patterns
3. Avoid duplication
4. Maintain compatibility
5. Preserve functionality

NEVER generate temporary patch scripts.
Modify files directly using proper refactoring.
